Tuesday 17th September 2013 until further notice. 

A temporary overbridge has been installed at New Cross Gate between platforms 1/ 2 and 3/ 4.ã€€ This is part of a Network Rail "Access for All" programme which will eventually see 3 new lifts installed at the station.

From Tuesday 17th September 2013, the normal staircase from platforms 1 & 2 up to the ticket hall will be blocked out of use. This will mean anyone disembarking on platforms 1 & 2 will be required to use the temporary overbridge at the London End of the platform and cross onto platforms 3 & 4 to exit the station via the original staircase.
